Uses of Package
suncertify.db

Packages that use suncertify.db
suncertify.db Provides interfaces and classes for working with the DB interface and its Data implementation. 
suncertify.protocol Provides interfaces and classes for working with Subcontractor objects and the SubcontractorCommand protocol. 
suncertify.protocol.client Provides classes for developing local and remote (RMI) clients based on the SubcontractorCommand protocol. 
 

Classes in suncertify.db used by suncertify.db
Data.FieldDescriptor
          The FieldDescriptor class encapsulates the descriptions of individual database fields.
DB
          This is the DB interface for Bodgitt and Scarper, LLC.
DuplicateKeyException
          Instances of the DuplicateKeyException class are thrown to indicate that the software has attempted to create a record that would create a duplicate key condition.
InvalidDataHeaderException
          Instances of the InvalidDataHeaderException class are thrown to indicate that a database header is invalid.
InvalidMagicCookieException
          Instances of the InvalidMagicCookieException class are thrown to indicate that a database file magic cookie does not match the expected value.
RecordNotFoundException
          Instances of the RecordNotFoundException class are thrown to indicate that the software has specified a record that does not exist or is marked as deleted in a database file.
